         <abstract>
            <p>We consider Gauss quadrature formulae $Q_n, n \in \mathbf{N}$, approximating the integral $I(f):= \int^1_{-1} w(x)f(x)dx, w = W/p_i, i = 1, 2$, with $W(x) = (1 - x)^\alpha(1 + x)^\beta, \alpha, \beta = \pm1/2$ and $p_1(x) = 1 + a^2 + 2ax, p_2(x) = (2b + 1)x^2 + b^2, b &gt; 0$. In certain spaces of analytic functions the error functional $R_n:= I - Q_n$ is continuous. In [1] and [2] estimates for $\|R_n\|$ are given for a wide class of weight functions. Here, for a restricted class of weight functions, we calculate the norm of $R_n$ explicitly.</p>
          </abstract>
